The country is now run by a nominally civilian government, but it is heavily stacked with former military personnel, many of whom are opposed to further liberalisation.

Downing Street had hoped to keep the visit secret until Mr  Cameron’s arrival but information was released yesterday by the Burmese Government and the NLD.

The trip will cap a week-long trade mission to the Far East in which the Prime Minister will try to get his premiership back on track.

