Mr Cameron, who is being  accompanied by 35 British leaders, will today look to boost trade  during talks in Japan with Prime Minister Yoshihiko Noda.

He will announce new Japanese investment deals, including one with Nissan worth more than £200million, creating almost 1,500 new jobs in the UK and safeguarding thousands more.

Mr Cameron said: ‘Nissan’s  investment in the UK is a huge vote of confidence in the skills and  flexibility of our workforce.’ 

